trans-unit.source: npm is written to use resources efficiently on install, and part of this is that it tries to do as many things concurrently as is practical. If you see ENOENT lstat, ENOENT chmod, ENOTEMPTY unlink, or something similar in your log output, try updating npm to the latest version. If the problem persists, look at npm/npm#6043 and see if somebody has already discussed your issue.

trans-unit.source: where A is some version of a package, and A' is a different version of the same package. Because B depends on a different version of A than the one that is already in the tree, it must install a separate copy. The same is true of A', which must install B'. Because B' depends on the original version of A, which has been overridden, the cycle falls into infinite regress.
trans-unit.target: 여기서 A 는 패키지의 일부 버전이고 A' 는 동일한 패키지의 다른 버전입니다. 때문에 B 가 다른 버전에 따라 달라집니다 트리에 이미있는 것보다, 별도의 사본을 설치해야합니다. B' 를 설치해야하는 A' 도 마찬가지입니다 . B' 는 재정 의 된 A 의 원래 버전에 의존 하기 때문에 주기는 무한 회귀에 빠집니다. A
